illdesc=Briefly stops wild Pokémon from taking action.\n}}\n{{Spindata/Shuffle|col=3|type=Fighting|ndex=538|num=141\n|min=60\n|max=120\n|raisemaxlevel=10\n|skill=Power of 5\n|skilldesc=Increases damage when you make a match of five.\n|swapper=Barrier Bash+\n}}\n|-\n{{Spindata/GO|col=6|type=Fighting|ndex=538\n|hatch=N/A\n|buddy=5\n|evolution=N/A\n|stamina=260\n|attack=172\n|defense=160\n|fast={{m|Low Kick}}, {{m|Zen Headbutt}}\n|special={{m|Focus Blast}}, {{m|Low Sweep}}, {{m|Body Slam}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-1\n|type1=Fighting\n|pictype=art\n|no1=538\n|name1=Throh\n|type1-1=Fighting}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Fighting}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=538}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=538}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=538}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|538|Throh}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Throh and {{p|Sawk}} draw parallels to the [[Generation I]] Pokémon {{p|Hitmonlee}} and {{p|Hitmonchan}}, in that they are male-only {{type|Fighting}} Pokémon that appear to be related to each other.\n* In both the anime and [[PokéPark 2: Wonders Beyond]], Throh is slightly taller than Sawk despite being four inches (10 centimetres) shorter than it according to the [[Pokédex]].\n* Throh and its {{p|Sawk|counterpart}} were designed by [[Ken Sugimori]].\n* Throh was designed before Sawk, having been repurposed from an unused Gen 4 design.\n\n===Origin===\nThroh is based on a {{wp|judo}} expert or \'\'judoka\'\', and an \'\'{{wp|oni}}\'\'.\n\nAccording to interviews with [[Ken Sugimori]] in \'\'Nintendo Dream\'\', in development, Sawk and Throh both had horns, making them look more like \'\'oni\'\'. However, they were replaced with eyebrows so as not to clash with {{p|Tornadus}} and {{p|Thundurus}}, who both were originally designed to be red and blue, like Throh and Sawk.\n\n====Name origin====\nThroh is a corruption of \'\'throw\'\'.\n\nNageki is a combination of 投げる \'\'nageru\'\' (to throw) and 撃 \'\'geki\'\' (strike). It may also involve 鬼 \'\'ki\'\' ({{wp|Oni (folklore)|demon}}).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Fighting|type2=Fighting\n|ja=ナゲキ \'\'Nageki\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|投げる \'\'nageru\'\'|to throw}} and {{tt|撃 \'\'geki\'\'|strike}}. May also involve {{tt|鬼 \'\'ki\'\'|demon}}.\n|de=Jiutesto|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Jujutsu|Jiu Jitsu}}\'\' and {{tt|\'\'Testosteron\'\'|Testosterone}}\n|fr=Judokrak|frmeaning=From \'\'judoka\'\' and the onomatopoeia \'\'crack\'\'\n|es=Throh|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Throh|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=던지미 \'\'Deonjimi\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|던짐 \'\'deonjim\'\'|throwing}} and suffix {{tt|-이 \'\'i\'\'|-er}}\n|zh_cmn=投射鬼 \'\'Tóushèguǐ\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|投射 \'\'tóushè\'\'|throw, fling}} and the Japanese 鬼 \'\'ki\'\' ({{wp|Oni_(folklore)|oni}}).\n|ru=Трох \'\'Trokh\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fighting|prevnum=537|prev=Seismitoad|nextnum=539|next=Sawk}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Jiutesto]]\n[[es:Throh]]\n[[fr:Judokrak]]\n[[it:Throh]]\n[[ja:ナゲキ]]\n[[zh:投摔鬼]]'}